 

'''Josephine Akosua Adomako Ampofo'''  y''ɛ'' Ghanani nhomsuamu ɔbenfo a  ɔkyer''ɛ'' ade fa bɔbiasu ho wɔ suapɔn a ''ɛ''ne University of Ghana<ref>Akosua Adomako Ampofo Bio (africanstudies.org)</ref><ref>Professor Akosua Adomako Ampofo | Institute of African Studies | University of Ghana (ug.edu.gh)</ref>. ɔy''ɛ'' obi a ɔko ma mma yiyedie,na afei nso, ɔpere ma nnipa yiyie die<ref>Prof. Akosua Adomako Ampofo – Professor of African and Gender studies – Ghana – Young African Women Congress (yawcafrica.org)</ref>.

== Ne mmofrase ne nhomasua ==
Ampofo maame y''ɛ'' Germanini na ne papa y''ɛ'' Ghanani a ofiri Asanteman mu. Ne papa abusua no y''ɛ'' nea wɔdɔm amanykuo a ''ɛ''de Converntions Peoples Party (CPP). Ampofo kɔɔ ntoaso sukuu a ''ɛ''ne Aburi Girl's Secondary school. Ampofo nyaa suapɔn abɔdin krataa a edikan firi sapɔn a ''ɛ''de Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology, bre a owie n'adesua a ''ɛ''fa adansie ho nnema no. ɔtoa so suaa ade faa mpontuo nhyehyɛeɛ ho ma no nyaa abodin krataa a ''ɛ''ne Master Degree. Ampofo nyaa suapɔn abɔdin a ''ɛ''kɔ anim a ''ɛ''ne Phd fri suapɔn a ''ɛ''de Vanderbilt University bre a owiee n'adesua a ''ɛ''fa nnipa nney''ɛ''e ho no. ɔsan nso kura abɔdin krataa a ene Post-Graduate Diploma a onya firii suapɔn a ''ɛ''de Technical Universit of Dortmond, a ''ɛ''wɔ Germany.

== Nhomasua mu Adwuma ==
Ampofo hy''ɛ'' adekyere ase wɔ University of Ghana wɔ afe 1989. Wo afe 1994 ne 1995 ntam no, na okura dibea a ''ɛ''ne Junior Fulbright. Wɔ afe 2005 mu no, ɔb''ɛ''y''ɛɛ'' ɔbaa odikan s''ɛ'' otitenani wɔ suapɔn no fa bi a ''ɛ''de Centre for Gender Studies and Advocacy (CEGENSA), okuraa saa dibea no kosii afe 2009 mu. Wɔ afe 2008 mu no, ɔb''ɛ''y''ɛɛ'' koowaa krataa mu samufoɔ kowaa krataa a ''ɛ''ne Ghana Studies, na okuraa saa dibea no kosii afe 2013 mu. ɔsan nso y''ɛɛ'' adwuma s''ɛ'' koowaa krataa mu samufoɔ  ma Contemporary Journal of African Studies.

Na ɔy''ɛ'' Mellon Fellow wɔ afe 2014 mu wɔ University of Cape Coast Town, faako a ɔy''ɛ'' adwuma ma Centre for African Studies. Wɔ afe 2015 mu no, ɔy''ɛɛ'' adwuma s''ɛ'' Senior Fulbright Scholar-in-Residence a ''ɛ''wo suapɔn a ''ɛ''ne Concordia University Irvine. 

ɔy''ɛ'' adwuma s''ɛ'' Kohunufo maa nwumakuo a ''ɛ''mu bi ne [[:en:United_Nations_Development_Fund_for_Women|UNIFEM]], [[:en:UNICEF|UNICEF]], [[:en:World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization (WHO)]], [[:en:Save_the_Children|Save the Children]], [[:en:Joint_United_Nations_Programme_on_HIV/AIDS|UNAIDS]], [[:en:Ministry_of_Women_and_Children's_Affairs|Ministry for Gender & Social Protection, Ghana]]; Participatory Development Associates; Gender Studies and Human Rights Documentation Centre and [[:en:Kofi_Annan_International_Peacekeeping_Training_Centre|Kofi Annan International Peacekeeping Training Centre]].

== Adwumakuo a ɔdom ==
Wɔ afe 2019 mu no, s''ɛ'' okandifo ma African Studies Association of Africa (ASAA) no, ɔhw''ɛ'' maa wɔy''ɛ'' nyiamu a edikan wɔ East Africa. Ampofo ka wɔn a wɔhyehy''ɛɛ''  ekuo a ''ɛ''de ASAA a wɔhyehy''ɛe'' wɔ afe 2013 mu no. ɔsan nso dɔm akuo ahorɔw a ''ɛ''de Association and Sociologists for Women and Society, (SWS), [[:en:African_Studies_Association|African Studies Association]], United States, Ghana Domestic Violence Coalition, the Network for Women's Rights in Ghana, the Council for Social Science Research in Africa (CODESRIA)  ne[[:en:International_Sociological_Association|International Sociological Association, (ISA)]]. ɔsan nso dɔm ekuo a ''ɛ''de [[:en:Ghana_Academy_of_Arts_and_Sciences|Ghana Academy of Arts and Sciences]]

